<div class="ui raised very padded text container segment">
    <h2 class="ui header">Plane Ticket Choices</h2>
    <h4 class="ui header">XNA-PTY</h4>
    <p>This could be the easiest choice, but not necessarily the cheapest. XNA is a smaller airport, which makes plane tickets a bit more expensive. 
    However, if you decide to go this route, try to track American Airlines (usually the cheapest option from XNA) about a month before the day you 
    plan to leave as this is usually the time ticket prices drop down.</p>
    <h4 class="ui header">DFW-PTY</h4>
    <p>This is our recommended choice. Usually connections from XNA include DFW, so flying out from DFW could cut your ticket price dramatically. 
    This strategy could also work with any other major airport you are closest to. At DFW, in particular, there is an airline that has been awesome to us called Spirit Airlines. 
    It’s a low-cost airline, with extremely reliable planes and service. You don’t get to bring 
    tons of luggage with them, because they charge bags separately and at a very high price. If you can get by with minimal luggage, this might be the best option for 
    you. <a target="_blank" href="https://www.spirit.com/Default.aspx">You can check them out here!</a></p>
    <div class="ui section divider"></div>
    <p>Which ever option you decide, we strongly recommend you use two flight searching tools to look for the best deals on tickets:</p>
    <div class="ui bulleted list">
        <a class="item" target="_blank" href="https://www.skyscanner.com/">Skyscanner</a>
        <a class="item" target="_blank" href="https://www.google.com/flights/">Google Flights</a>
    </div>
</div>

